text: In short, enterprise sales cycles are a lot longer and involve many more people than SMB and mid-market sales. I find that you not only have to serve each persona content to serve their needs, but also content that helps bring all the disparate priorities in alignment, which is pretty tough. Enterprise buyers also tend to have a more sophisticated strategy and set of needs, some work with a center of excellence for their tech, others have a tech stack unique to each BU, etc. There's a lot of variability and the sales team in particular needs to feed their champions and skeptics a ton of content to get through that 6/9/12/18 month sales cycle. Not to mention procurement and security requirements!
